Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.94,0:29:41.70,English,,0,0,0,,Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu Ubuntu question okay\N{\rChinese}乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图 乌班图
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.70,0:29:44.56,English,,0,0,0,,so the question is isn't food scarce because\N{\rChinese}所以问题是：食物不稀缺吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.56,0:29:47.72,English,,0,0,0,,food is a finite resource right do\N{\rChinese}食物是有限资源，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.72,0:29:51.14,English,,0,0,0,,yourself a favor okay go to the\N{\rChinese}给自己一个小忙，去北京的垃圾堆里找找
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.14,0:29:54.26,English,,0,0,0,,garbage dump somewhere anywhere in beijing and\N{\rChinese}garbage dump somewhereanywhere in beijing and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.26,0:29:55.60,English,,0,0,0,,see the amount of food that\N{\rChinese}看一下食物的量
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.60,0:30:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,is wasted every single day if food was scarce why do we have food waste\N{\rChinese}每天都有食物被浪费，如果食物稀缺，为什么还会有浪费？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.72,0:30:04.94,English,,0,0,0,,okay so if you just do the mathematics what you will\N{\rChinese}好的，那如果你只做数学，你会得到什么
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.94,0:30:07.02,English,,0,0,0,,discover is there's enough food to\N{\rChinese}发现有足够的食物可以
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.02,0:30:12.80,English,,0,0,0,,feed everyone okay it doesn't have to be hunger and\N{\rChinese}给大家吃饭，没必要是饥饿
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.80,0:30:18.40,English,,0,0,0,,starvation it's an artificial crisis it doesn't make sense\N{\rChinese}饥饿是人为的危机，毫无意义
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.40,0:30:21.96,English,,0,0,0,,so you're right in that yeah the food is not infinite but\N{\rChinese}所以你说得对，食物不是无限的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.96,0:30:24.34,English,,0,0,0,,it's abundant there's a lot of it\N{\rChinese}它很丰富，数量很多
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.34,0:30:29.36,English,,0,0,0,,enough to feed people okay okay\N{\rChinese}足够供人吃饭，好的，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.36,0:30:37.56,English,,0,0,0,,okay okay all right um\N{\rChinese}好的，好的，没问题
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.56,0:30:42.56,English,,0,0,0,,so again you guys are stuck in the scarcity mindset um\N{\rChinese}于是你们又陷入了稀缺心态，嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.56,0:30:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,and it's very convincing so\N{\rChinese}而且这点很有说服力
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.76,0:30:48.70,English,,0,0,0,,let's move on okay\N{\rChinese}好了，继续吧
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.70,0:30:51.12,English,,0,0,0,,so this is this is something that\N{\rChinese}这就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.12,0:30:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,we'll go back to later on okay because\N{\rChinese}我们稍后再回到这点，好的，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.26,0:30:56.06,English,,0,0,0,,i cannot convince you today this morning that\N{\rChinese}今天早上我还说不服你
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.06,0:30:58.80,English,,0,0,0,,everything you believed about the world about yourself is\N{\rChinese}你对世界、对自己的所有认知都已是错的，嗯你仍然停留在那种稀缺心态，嗯。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.80,0:31:03.78,English,,0,0,0,,wrong okay you're still stuck there like okay there's scarcity um\N{\rChinese}wrong okay you're still stuck there like okay there's scarcity um
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.78,0:31:06.50,English,,0,0,0,,and you're right there's scarcity but\N{\rChinese}而你说的没错，确实有稀缺，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.50,0:31:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,we also live in a world of abundance okay and a lot of things\N{\rChinese}我们也生活在一个充满的世界里，嗯，很多事物都充足了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.48,0:31:14.12,English,,0,0,0,,that you believe are just misconceptions about the world okay\N{\rChinese}你认为的只是关于世界的误解，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.12,0:31:16.80,English,,0,0,0,,so so we'll go back there okay later on all right so\N{\rChinese}于是我们稍后再回到那点，好的，全部都明白了，嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.80,0:31:18.02,English,,0,0,0,,let's move on okay so\N{\rChinese}好了，接着说，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.02,0:31:21.20,English,,0,0,0,,we've done money now right now let's do another\N{\rChinese}我们已经谈过钱了，现在再来一个
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.20,0:31:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,question let's do a question of happiness\N{\rChinese}再来一个关于幸福的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.02,0:31:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,the question\N{\rChinese}问题
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.66,0:31:31.74,English,,0,0,0,,for us today is what makes us happy\N{\rChinese}今天对我们来说，是什么让我们快乐？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.94,0:31:36.62,English,,0,0,0,,come on what makes you happy how can you live a happy life\N{\rChinese}来吧，是什么让你快乐？你怎样才能过上快乐的生活？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.84,0:31:43.62,English,,0,0,0,,well obviously money right you have a lot\N{\rChinese}嗯，显然是钱，对吧，你有很多钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.62,0:31:45.52,English,,0,0,0,,of money that's gonna make you happy what else\N{\rChinese}钱的事能让你开心，还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.46,0:31:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,exactly power right sure power\N{\rChinese}正是权力，对吧，权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.60,0:31:55.22,English,,0,0,0,,excuse me freedom okay\N{\rChinese}请问自由呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.22,0:31:59.28,English,,0,0,0,,good freedom yeah what\N{\rChinese}好的，自由，嗯，什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.28,0:32:01.94,English,,0,0,0,,else relationships yep sure\N{\rChinese}还有什么？关系，嗯，好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.20,0:32:10.42,English,,0,0,0,,you have good friends right like lots and lots of friends what else\N{\rChinese}你有好朋友，对吧，很多很多朋友，还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.98,0:32:18.86,English,,0,0,0,,okay love right love sure what\N{\rChinese}好的，爱吧，爱，没错，爱，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.86,0:32:21.14,English,,0,0,0,,else like video games i guess\N{\rChinese}还有什么？比如视频游戏，我猜吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.08,0:32:24.82,English,,0,0,0,,vacations okay lots and\N{\rChinese}假期，好多了
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.82,0:32:28.34,English,,0,0,0,,lots of things okay what you will discover about this list is this\N{\rChinese}好多事，好的，你会发现这份清单的内容是这样的：
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.84,0:32:34.88,English,,0,0,0,,you are thinking about individuals you are thinking about people you are thinking about people you are thinking about people you are thinking about people happiness\N{\rChinese}你在想个体，你在想人，你在想人，你在想人，你在想人，幸福。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.36,0:32:45.60,English,,0,0,0,,and this is actually unique in human history\N{\rChinese}这点实际上在人类历史上是独一无二的。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.60,0:32:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,if you if you go back in time to five five years ago\N{\rChinese}如果你回到五年前
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.90,0:32:52.18,English,,0,0,0,,and\N{\rChinese}然后
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.18,0:32:55.42,English,,0,0,0,,you ask people how can you be\N{\rChinese}你问人们怎么做
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.42,0:32:58.14,English,,0,0,0,,happy they would focus more\N{\rChinese}他们会更专注
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.14,0:33:02.92,English,,0,0,0,,on collective happiness in other words if your community is happy you're going to be happy\N{\rChinese}在其他方面就是如果你的社区开心，你也会开心
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.92,0:33:09.56,English,,0,0,0,,same same\N{\rChinese}同样同样
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.56,0:33:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,same same same same same same same same same same same\N{\rChinese}同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.54,0:33:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,same same same same same same same same same same same same same\N{\rChinese}同样同样
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.08,0:33:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same\N{\rChinese}同样同样
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.16,0:33:23.68,English,,0,0,0,,same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same same\N{\rChinese}同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.68,0:33:27.96,English,,0,0,0,,same same same same same same same same same same\N{\rChinese}同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.96,0:33:32.64,English,,0,0,0,,same same same same same same same same Happiness meant helping others,\N{\rChinese}同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同样同
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.88,0:33:34.28,English,,0,0,0,,being generous to others.\N{\rChinese}对他人慷慷大方
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.18,0:33:39.02,English,,0,0,0,,So for example, let's just say\N{\rChinese}比如说
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.02,0:33:41.46,English,,0,0,0,,that I go off\N{\rChinese}于是我走了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.90,0:33:46.18,English,,0,0,0,,and I wonder and then I find a lot of gold, right?\N{\rChinese}我想想，然后我发现很多金子，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.30,0:33:49.98,English,,0,0,0,,I come back and what's the first thing I do with all this gold?\N{\rChinese}我回来了，先把这堆金子做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.14,0:33:52.88,English,,0,0,0,,Do you guys know? And this is like the ancient past.\N{\rChinese}你们知道吗？这就是古代的做法。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.20,0:33:55.08,English,,0,0,0,,Dig a hole and put them inside.\N{\rChinese}挖个坑，把钱放进去。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.40,0:33:57.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, yeah, good, right?\N{\rChinese}好的，行吧，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.10,0:34:00.74,English,,0,0,0,,We're gonna dig a hole and put that money inside because we wanna give to our children.\N{\rChinese}我们要挖个坑，把钱放进去，给孩子们用。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.98,0:34:03.90,English,,0,0,0,,That's a modern mindset. But what did they do before?\N{\rChinese}那是现代心态。那之前他们做了什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.66,0:34:08.22,English,,0,0,0,,And this happened throughout every society.\N{\rChinese}这在各个社会都发生过。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.48,0:34:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,If I became rich one day, what's the first thing I would do?\N{\rChinese}如果我有一天变得很富有，我第一件事会做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.10,0:34:13.50,English,,0,0,0,,Show off? Hmm?\N{\rChinese}炫耀？嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.62,0:34:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,Show off? No, okay, so we'll learn this, okay?\N{\rChinese}炫耀？不，好的，那我们来学这个，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.72,0:34:21.62,English,,0,0,0,,But the first thing that people did was they had a big feast for everyone.\N{\rChinese}但人们最先做的事是给大家办一场大宴会。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.72,0:34:24.66,English,,0,0,0,,They spent all the money on a big feast.\N{\rChinese}他们把所有的钱都花在了一场大宴会上。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.46,0:34:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,Because what mattered was, your reputation within the community.\N{\rChinese}因为重要的是，你在社区里的声誉。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.06,0:34:30.68,English,,0,0,0,,What mattered was your generosity.\N{\rChinese}重要的是你的慷慨。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.92,0:34:34.40,English,,0,0,0,,If you got rich one day, you made sure that\N{\rChinese}如果你有一天变得很富有，你会确保……
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.40,0:34:37.40,English,,0,0,0,,everyone in the community benefited from your wealth,\N{\rChinese}社区里的每个人都能从你的财富中受益。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.02,0:34:40.64,English,,0,0,0,,usually by holding a big feast.\N{\rChinese}通常通过办一场大宴会来完成。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.56,0:34:46.70,English,,0,0,0,,And guess what, guys? This is true in China for most of Chinese history,\N{\rChinese}你们猜怎么回事？这在中国大部分历史里都是真的，right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.84,0:34:48.32,English,,0,0,0,,right?\N{\rChinese}right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.94,0:34:52.62,English,,0,0,0,,If you come from a Chinese village, come to Beijing,\N{\rChinese}如果你来自中国的一个小村庄，来到北京，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.04,0:34:56.78,English,,0,0,0,,you open a restaurant, you make a lot of money, you go out to your village, what's the first thing you do?\N{\rChinese}你开了一家餐馆，赚了很多钱，回到自己的村庄，第一件事是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.84,0:35:00.64,English,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys. You have a big feast for everyone.\N{\rChinese}来吧，伙计们。你给大家办一场大宴会。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.32,0:35:04.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is ingrained in us, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，这已经根深蒂固在我们心里了，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.10,0:35:08.34,English,,0,0,0,,But as you say, today, what we believe is,\N{\rChinese}正如你所说，今天我们所信的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.48,0:35:11.52,English,,0,0,0,,if you have a lot of money, put it underground or put it in a bank, okay?\N{\rChinese}如果你有很多钱，放进地下或存进银行，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.86,0:35:15.94,English,,0,0,0,,But back then, for most of human history, we would just spend it all on a big feast.\N{\rChinese}但那时，几乎人类历史的那段时间里，我们只会把钱全部花在一场大宴会上。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.74,0:35:21.20,English,,0,0,0,,We wanted everyone to share in happiness, and that's what made us happy,\N{\rChinese}我们想让大家一起共享喜悦，这就是让我们开心的原因，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.30,0:35:24.10,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.84,0:35:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions? Yeah?\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.36,0:35:34.92,English,,0,0,0,,I was wondering, you mentioned that\N{\rChinese}我在想，你刚才说过
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.20,0:35:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,it was for reputation on some levels.\N{\rChinese}它在某些层面上是关于声誉的。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.26,0:35:44.12,English,,0,0,0,,Would that count into as individual happiness?\N{\rChinese}那算作个人幸福吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.38,0:35:47.80,English,,0,0,0,,Because after you get rich, you care about your reputation.\N{\rChinese}因为你一富起来就会在乎自己的声誉。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.74,0:35:52.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, yeah, so you're asking, is this about individual reputation?\N{\rChinese}好的，回到问题：这关乎个人声誉吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.16,0:35:54.62,English,,0,0,0,,And again, I mean, this is hard, okay?\N{\rChinese}再说一次，我是说这很难，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.84,0:35:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,But the individual reputation is not about the individual, the concept of individual did not exist before.\N{\rChinese}但个人声誉不是关于个人，个人的概念在之前还不存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.90,0:36:00.64,English,,0,0,0,,We just created it.\N{\rChinese}我们刚刚才创造了它。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.48,0:36:05.64,English,,0,0,0,,The idea that I'm a person independent of my family, independent of my community,\N{\rChinese}我独立于家族、社区、周遭世界的想法毫无意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.38,0:36:09.58,English,,0,0,0,,independent of the world around me, makes no sense.\N{\rChinese}过去对你最严重的惩罚是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.42,0:36:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,What was the worst punishment that could be inflicted on you in the past?\N{\rChinese}What was the worst punishment that could be inflicted on you in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.66,0:36:17.68,English,,0,0,0,,Let's just say that we're gonna fight, I kill you, right?\N{\rChinese}我们就说吧，咱们要打了，我会杀了你，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.50,0:36:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,You're, they say you are no longer belong to this world.\N{\rChinese}你啊，他们说你已经不属于这个世界了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.54,0:36:24.90,English,,0,0,0,,Exactly, banishment, exile.\N{\rChinese}正是如此，流放，流放。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.46,0:36:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,You're, they say you are no longer belong to this world. death, right? And today, if I killed you, the police would come catch me and then kill me.\N{\rChinese}你啊，他们说你已经不属于这个世界了。死亡，对吧？今天如果我杀了你，警察就会来抓我，然后再杀我。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.34,0:36:33.40,English,,0,0,0,,But before, we didn't do that because the worst thing\N{\rChinese}但之前我们没这么做，因为最糟的事是把你流放。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.40,0:36:35.66,English,,0,0,0,,that we could do was exile you.\N{\rChinese}我们能做的最糟的事就是把你流放。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.70,0:36:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,It says, you're no longer part of us.\N{\rChinese}它说，你已经不再是我们的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.90,0:36:40.86,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? So the concept of individuality did not exist,\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？所以个体的概念并不存在，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.12,0:36:42.88,English,,0,0,0,,right?\N{\rChinese}对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.34,0:36:47.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's move on.\N{\rChinese}好的，接下来继续。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.06,0:36:49.26,English,,0,0,0,,All right, so\N{\rChinese}好的，开始吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.26,0:36:53.32,English,,0,0,0,,now I'm going to present two understandings of the world\N{\rChinese}现在我要给出两种对世界的理解
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.32,0:36:57.46,English,,0,0,0,,and you're going to tell me which understanding you think is correct.\N{\rChinese}你要告诉我哪一种理解是正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.72,0:36:58.94,English,,0,0,0,,And the first understanding,\N{\rChinese}第一种理解是，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.80,0:37:03.32,English,,0,0,0,,we humans don't have agency.\N{\rChinese}我们人类没有主导权。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.38,0:37:04.92,English,,0,0,0,,We don't have really control. Why?\N{\rChinese}我们真的没有控制。为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.04,0:37:07.30,English,,0,0,0,,Because there are powerful gods out there, okay?\N{\rChinese}因为外面有强大的神啊，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.58,0:37:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,There are these powerful gods like Apollo,\N{\rChinese}有这些强大的神，如阿波罗，多尼修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.18,0:37:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,Dionysus.\N{\rChinese}有这些强大的神，如阿波罗，多尼修斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.16,0:37:15.24,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, the problem though is that\N{\rChinese}哦，问题在于
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.40,0:37:21.18,English,,0,0,0,,they are also controlled by other gods that are more powerful, like for example, fate.\N{\rChinese}它们也被更强大的神控制，例如命运。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.42,0:37:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,Fortune. And\N{\rChinese}命运。然后
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.40,0:37:29.56,English,,0,0,0,,then there are these really ancient gods\N{\rChinese}接着有这些非常古老的神
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.56,0:37:31.98,English,,0,0,0,,that control the structure of the universe.\N{\rChinese}它们掌控宇宙结构。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.16,0:37:36.56,English,,0,0,0,,For example, maybe anger and pride.\N{\rChinese}例如，愤怒与自负。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.62,0:37:40.54,English,,0,0,0,,So you obviously know individual agency\N{\rChinese}所以你显然知道个体行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.54,0:37:44.72,English,,0,0,0,,because there's always a god screwing with you, okay?\N{\rChinese}因为总有神在玩弄你，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.16,0:37:47.26,English,,0,0,0,,You might get rich, but then\N{\rChinese}你可能会富有，但随后
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.26,0:37:50.80,English,,0,0,0,,the god of pride looks at you and says, no, no, no.\N{\rChinese}自负之神看着你说，没，没，没。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.84,0:37:52.30,English,,0,0,0,,I need to teach this mortal a lesson.\N{\rChinese}我得给这凡人上一课。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.56,0:37:55.12,English,,0,0,0,,So you're not going to control the world. The god comes into me,\N{\rChinese}于是你就不会去掌控世界。神会降临我身，令我自负，随后我就搞砸了，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.22,0:37:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,makes me too arrogant, and I screw up, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是我们总是被这些超出我们理解的力量所控制。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.20,0:38:03.12,English,,0,0,0,,So we're always being controlled by these forces beyond our understanding.\N{\rChinese}我们是神经，产生记忆，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.80,0:38:06.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's the first worldview.\N{\rChinese}好的，那就是第一个世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.28,0:38:08.84,English,,0,0,0,,The second worldview is this.\N{\rChinese}第二个世界观是这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.40,0:38:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,We are synapses that\N{\rChinese}我们是突触。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.84,0:38:16.28,English,,0,0,0,,generate memories,\N{\rChinese}生成记忆，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.44,0:38:20.04,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.70,0:38:22.06,English,,0,0,0,,We are memories.\N{\rChinese}我们是记忆。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.40,0:38:24.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We are memories. Our understanding is that we are synapses that generate memories. Our understanding of the world comes from our experience.\N{\rChinese}好的？我们是记忆。我们的理解是我们是产生记忆的突触。我们对世界的理解来自我们的经验。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.26,0:38:27.34,English,,0,0,0,,That is controlled by synapses.\N{\rChinese}那是由突触控制的。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.88,0:38:31.68,English,,0,0,0,,Synapses come from a combination of DNA\N{\rChinese}突触来自DNA的组合。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.68,0:38:35.00,English,,0,0,0,,and environment.\N{\rChinese}和环境。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.54,0:38:40.38,English,,0,0,0,,Our genes and our interaction with the environment, our experiences.\N{\rChinese}我们的基因与与环境的互动，我们的经历。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.54,0:38:43.64,English,,0,0,0,,And what this means is that\N{\rChinese}这意味着的事是：
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.64,0:38:48.76,English,,0,0,0,,we can now have control over our own individual fate.\N{\rChinese}我们现在可以掌控自己的命运。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.96,0:38:53.30,English,,0,0,0,,If you're angry, it's because some experience is not going to control you.\N{\rChinese}如果你生气，那是因为某些经历不再掌控你。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.30,0:38:58.06,English,,0,0,0,,So we're not going to control you. There's someone being Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub\N{\rChinese}于是我们不再掌控你。有人在掌控着。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.06,0:39:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub\N{\rChinese}乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌布乌
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.66,0:39:04.58,English,,0,0,0,,Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub\N{\rChinese}Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.58,0:39:09.18,English,,0,0,0,,Ub Ub\N{\rChinese}乌布乌布
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.18,0:39:15.22,English,,0,0,0,,Ub Ub\N{\rChinese}乌布乌布
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.22,0:39:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub Ub there are lots\N{\rChinese}有很多
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.12,0:39:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,and lots of gods, they're evil and\N{\rChinese}还有许多神祇，它们是邪恶的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.96,0:39:25.94,English,,0,0,0,,they're random and\N{\rChinese}它们是随机的，并且
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.94,0:39:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,we have absolutely no control over our fate.\N{\rChinese}我们完全没有掌控命运的能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.68,0:39:32.78,English,,0,0,0,,We can only hope to get lucky in life and not piss off the gods.\N{\rChinese}我们只能祈祷人生顺遂，免得惹神怒
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.26,0:39:34.92,English,,0,0,0,,In the second worldview,\N{\rChinese}在第二个世界观中，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.16,0:39:38.08,English,,0,0,0,,we are only a collection of our memories\N{\rChinese}我们只是记忆的集合
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.08,0:39:40.44,English,,0,0,0,,and we are only synopsis.\N{\rChinese}而我们只是梗概。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.48,0:39:43.10,English,,0,0,0,,So we're able to manipulate the memories and\N{\rChinese}于是我们可以操纵记忆并
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.10,0:39:44.20,English,,0,0,0,,the synopsis in a proper way,\N{\rChinese}以正确的方式梗概，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.42,0:39:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,we can be free of all problems.\N{\rChinese}我们可以摆脱所有问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.90,0:39:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,We can be free of anger, we can be free of depression,\N{\rChinese}我们可以摆脱愤怒，我们可以摆脱抑郁，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.70,0:39:55.54,English,,0,0,0,,we can be free of misery.\N{\rChinese}我们可以摆脱苦难
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.70,0:39:59.06,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Let me ask you this question.\N{\rChinese}好的？让我问你一个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.84,0:40:02.92,English,,0,0,0,,Which worldview is a more accurate reflection of reality?\N{\rChinese}哪种世界观更准确地反映了现实？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.76,0:40:07.60,English,,0,0,0,,Obviously the second one, right? Because\N{\rChinese}显然是第二个，对吧？因为
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.60,0:40:09.58,English,,0,0,0,,this is neuroscience.\N{\rChinese}这就是神经科学。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.80,0:40:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,So, science or psychology or psychiatry.\N{\rChinese}所以，科学、心理学或精神病学。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.12,0:40:16.40,English,,0,0,0,,This is what you've been taught in school.\N{\rChinese}这就是你们在学校里学到的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.90,0:40:18.44,English,,0,0,0,,This is what you all believe.\N{\rChinese}这就是你们都相信的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.54,0:40:21.92,English,,0,0,0,,Our entire society is structured around this very idea.\N{\rChinese}我们的整个社会都围绕这个想法来构建。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.54,0:40:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,And what you will learn in this class is it is completely wrong.\N{\rChinese}而你在这门课里学到的内容完全是错的。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.56,0:40:31.82,English,,0,0,0,,It is the first one that is more accurate reflection of reality.\N{\rChinese}第一种说法更准确地反映了现实。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.44,0:40:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,The first one gives you more information,\N{\rChinese}第一句给你更多信息，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.66,0:40:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,gives you a more accurate assessment of how the world really works.\N{\rChinese}第二句给你更准确的评估，说明世界真正运作的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.42,0:40:46.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So now let me ask you this question.\N{\rChinese}好的？现在让我问你这个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.64,0:40:51.06,English,,0,0,0,,In the first worldview, and\N{\rChinese}在第一种世界观中，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.06,0:40:52.72,English,,0,0,0,,this is what we call polytheism.\N{\rChinese}这就是我们所说的多神论。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.96,0:40:57.86,English,,0,0,0,,And polytheism for most of human history was the dominant religion.\N{\rChinese}而在大多数人类历史中，多神论是主导宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.10,0:41:02.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now we live in a world where the religion is science.\N{\rChinese}好吧？现在我们生活在一个宗教就是科学的世界里。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.84,0:41:06.72,English,,0,0,0,,Science is basically religion. So,\N{\rChinese}科学基本上就是宗教。所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.72,0:41:07.96,English,,0,0,0,,why did we make the transition?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么做了这个转变？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.20,0:41:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,What's the benefit? If you're a powerful person, what would you prefer?\N{\rChinese}有什么好处？如果你是个有权势的人，你会更倾向什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.78,0:41:15.90,English,,0,0,0,,The second one as opposed to the first one?\N{\rChinese}第二个与第一个相对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.64,0:41:20.00,English,,0,0,0,,Why? What's the benefits to powerful people?\N{\rChinese}为什么？对有权势的人有什么好处？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.42,0:41:21.64,English,,0,0,0,,What is power?\N{\rChinese}什么是权力？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.30,0:41:24.60,English,,0,0,0,,Why do you believe the second one but not the first one?\N{\rChinese}你为什么相信第二个而不是第一个？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.22,0:41:29.30,English,,0,0,0,,They can blame you on failure and blame on fault.\N{\rChinese}他们会把失败和过错都怪在你身上。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.72,0:41:33.04,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay. Okay, so\N{\rChinese}好，好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.04,0:41:37.66,English,,0,0,0,,the idea of individual responsibility.\N{\rChinese}个体责任的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.26,0:41:42.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So then there's more control.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是就有更多控制。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.00,0:41:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,It's easier to control people in the system.\N{\rChinese}在系统中更容易掌控人们。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.90,0:41:51.20,English,,0,0,0,,Right? That's the first benefit.\N{\rChinese}对吗？那就是第一个好处。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.40,0:41:55.84,English,,0,0,0,,What's the second benefit? The second benefit is you will work harder, right?\N{\rChinese}第二个好处是什么？第二个好处是你会更努力工作，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.82,0:42:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,Because in the first system, you're like, you know what?\N{\rChinese}因为在第一个系统里，你就像……你知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.30,0:42:04.06,English,,0,0,0,,I don't need to go make a lot of money because\N{\rChinese}我不需要去赚很多钱，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.06,0:42:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,if I make a lot of money,\N{\rChinese}如果我赚了很多钱
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.70,0:42:10.80,English,,0,0,0,,the gods will punish me and make me proud.\N{\rChinese}神们会惩罚我并让我自豪。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.62,0:42:14.84,English,,0,0,0,,So I'm just going to like enjoy life and take it easy.\N{\rChinese}所以我就想好好享受生活，轻松一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.58,0:42:19.62,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So in the second system,\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以在第二个系统里，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.72,0:42:21.82,English,,0,0,0,,no, no, I have control over my own life.\N{\rChinese}不，不，我可以掌控自己的生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.96,0:42:25.50,English,,0,0,0,,So I need to work hard. Okay?\N{\rChinese}所以我需要努力工作。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.52,0:42:30.64,English,,0,0,0,,So again, the entire point of the system is to make you work as hard as possible\N{\rChinese}所以，整个系统的要点就是让你尽可能努力工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.64,0:42:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,because when you work hard, that generates real wealth for the powerful people.\N{\rChinese}因为努力工作会为强者创造真正的财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.80,0:42:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,Money does nothing. Okay?\N{\rChinese}钱什么也不做。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.56,0:42:38.44,English,,0,0,0,,Money just incentivizes you to work hard.\N{\rChinese}钱只是激励你努力工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.26,0:42:44.94,English,,0,0,0,,So this exists in order to make you work harder.\N{\rChinese}所以它的存在就是为了让你更努力工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.28,0:42:49.60,English,,0,0,0,,There's one more benefit or there's more benefits, but what's another benefit?\N{\rChinese}还有一个好处，或者说还有更多好处，但另一个好处是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.36,0:42:54.00,English,,0,0,0,,The other benefit is this.\N{\rChinese}另一个好处是这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.04,0:42:58.68,English,,0,0,0,,Powerlessness. Okay?\N{\rChinese}无力感。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.44,0:43:02.22,English,,0,0,0,,Powerlessness. It makes you powerless.\N{\rChinese}无力感。它让你变得无力。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.72,0:43:07.52,English,,0,0,0,,Why? This system is designed to make you absolutely powerless.\N{\rChinese}为什么？这个系统就是要让你完全无力。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.72,0:43:10.24,English,,0,0,0,,Why? You can't control anything.\N{\rChinese}为什么？你什么都控制不了。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.60,0:43:14.24,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Everything is controlled by gods and fate.\N{\rChinese}为什么？一切都由神与命运掌控。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.44,0:43:16.52,English,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.\N{\rChinese}不
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.52,0:43:20.62,English,,0,0,0,,See, see again, again, this is how you're brainwashed.\N{\rChinese}看，再看，再看，这就是你被洗脑的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.80,0:43:24.36,English,,0,0,0,,You believe one makes you powerless, but that's not correct.\N{\rChinese}你认为一是让你变成无力的。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.74,0:43:26.38,English,,0,0,0,,Two makes you powerless. Why?\N{\rChinese}二让你无力。为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.92,0:43:28.54,English,,0,0,0,,What's the difference between one and two?\N{\rChinese}一和二有什么区别？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.66,0:43:30.42,English,,0,0,0,,Why is it in number two? Number two, you are powerless.\N{\rChinese}为什么是二？二，你无力。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.72,0:43:34.32,English,,0,0,0,,You're playing the game that the, uh,\N{\rChinese}你在玩那个游戏，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.68,0:43:37.16,English,,0,0,0,,who has the power wants you to be powerless.\N{\rChinese}谁有权力就想让你无力。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.18,0:43:38.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.52,0:43:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,the problem with number two is you are incapable of collective action\N{\rChinese}问题在于二，你缺乏集体行动的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.50,0:43:46.26,English,,0,0,0,,because\N{\rChinese}因为
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.26,0:43:50.92,English,,0,0,0,,you think all sorts of your problems is the individual in you and that society.\N{\rChinese}你认为所有问题都来自你自己和社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.54,0:43:54.46,English,,0,0,0,,But number one, you are capable of collective action\N{\rChinese}但一号，你有集体行动的能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.46,0:43:57.70,English,,0,0,0,,and the only way to change the world is through collective action.\N{\rChinese}而改变世界的唯一方式就是集体行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.92,0:44:00.42,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? This is a really important point.\N{\rChinese}这样说通吗？这点非常重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.60,0:44:06.60,English,,0,0,0,,Two is designed to make you think the source of all your problems is within you.\N{\rChinese}二号设计让你认为所有问题的根源在于你自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.76,0:44:12.14,English,,0,0,0,,So you should ignore what other people do and think.\N{\rChinese}于是你应该忽略他人所作所为，专注于思考。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.28,0:44:13.58,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter to you.\N{\rChinese}这点对你没意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.86,0:44:21.34,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore you're incapable of identifying with other people.\N{\rChinese}于是你无法与他人产生共识。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.62,0:44:23.92,English,,0,0,0,,You're not capable of collective action.\N{\rChinese}你没有集体行动的能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.32,0:44:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,You're not capable of collective action and you feel really miserable.\N{\rChinese}你没有集体行动的能力，且感到非常难过。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.22,0:44:31.24,English,,0,0,0,,You're not capable of collective action. What you will do is play video\N{\rChinese}你没有集体行动的能力。你接下来会做的事是玩视频游戏或整天看黄片。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.24,0:44:34.90,English,,0,0,0,,games or watch porn all day.\N{\rChinese}你没有集体行动的能力。你接下来会做的事是玩视频游戏或整天看黄片。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.64,0:44:37.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And that's what's happening in society today.\N{\rChinese}好的。那就是今天社会里正在发生的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.76,0:44:40.72,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But in number two, like from experience,\N{\rChinese}是的。但在第二点，像经验那样，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.86,0:44:45.80,English,,0,0,0,,we would know that you should listen to the other's advice or,\N{\rChinese}我们会知道你应该听取别人的建议，或者说，你应该采纳别人的视角。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.96,0:44:49.88,English,,0,0,0,,you know, you should take others' perspectives\N{\rChinese}我们会知道你应该听取别人的建议，或者说，你应该采纳别人的视角。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.88,0:44:53.42,English,,0,0,0,,and not just...\N{\rChinese}并且不只是…
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.96,0:44:58.64,English,,0,0,0,,So in number two, who has authority?\N{\rChinese}于是第二点，谁有权威？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.64,0:45:01.56,English,,0,0,0,,Who do you listen to? You listen to scientists,\N{\rChinese}你听谁的？你听科学家。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.96,0:45:03.54,English,,0,0,0,,right? Scientists.\N{\rChinese}对吗？科学家。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.26,0:45:08.22,English,,0,0,0,,Because this system was created by scientists to trick you.\N{\rChinese}因为这个系统是科学家们创造的，专门用来骗你的。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.76,0:45:12.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. This system you think, oh, it's science.\N{\rChinese}好的。你认为这个系统是科学的。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.72,0:45:14.32,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore it must be real.\N{\rChinese}因此它一定是…
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.40,0:45:18.04,English,,0,0,0,,Guys, let me give you a piece of advice.\N{\rChinese}各位，给你们一句小建议。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.14,0:45:21.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. If you're ever feeling sad and\N{\rChinese}好的。如果你有时感到悲伤
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.64,0:45:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,you are depressed,\N{\rChinese}你很沮丧，
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.14,0:45:25.50,English,,0,0,0,,what should you do?\N{\rChinese}你该怎么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.32,0:45:30.34,English,,0,0,0,,What should you do? What have you been taught to do?\N{\rChinese}你该怎么做？你又被教会做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.14,0:45:32.46,English,,0,0,0,,You feel sad, you're depressed,\N{\rChinese}你感到悲伤，你很沮丧，
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.90,0:45:35.82,English,,0,0,0,,what should you do? Go to the nature.\N{\rChinese}去大自然
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.06,0:45:37.94,English,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Walk around.\N{\rChinese}嗯？走走吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.10,0:45:39.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Yeah. The correct answer is walk around.\N{\rChinese}好的。对，正确答案就是走走吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.96,0:45:42.20,English,,0,0,0,,But that's not what you've been taught, right? What have you been taught to do?\N{\rChinese}但这不是你被教会做的事，对吗？你又被教会做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.50,0:45:43.80,English,,0,0,0,,Telling your friend to your parent.\N{\rChinese}把你的朋友告诉给你的父母。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.82,0:45:45.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Telling your friend to your parent.\N{\rChinese}好的。把你的朋友告诉给你的父母。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.24,0:45:46.96,English,,0,0,0,,That's actually really good, right?\N{\rChinese}这其实真的很好，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.14,0:45:48.96,English,,0,0,0,,So walking around, exercising,\N{\rChinese}走走、锻炼、休息、跟朋友聊聊自己的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.66,0:45:52.90,English,,0,0,0,,resting, talking to a friend about your problem.\N{\rChinese}走走、锻炼、休息、跟朋友聊聊自己的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.00,0:45:54.80,English,,0,0,0,,That's all really good. But what have you been taught to do in school?\N{\rChinese}那也都很好。那你在学校学会做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.16,0:45:59.24,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Really? If you are feeling really, really sad, what should you do?\N{\rChinese}是吗？如果你真的很难过，应该怎么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.82,0:46:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,You should go talk to a psychiatrist, right?\N{\rChinese}你应该去找精神科医生，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.36,0:46:05.60,English,,0,0,0,,You should talk to a psychologist.\N{\rChinese}你应该去找心理学家。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.88,0:46:07.70,English,,0,0,0,,And what will he do? What will he or she do?\N{\rChinese}那他会做什么？他或她会做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.48,0:46:13.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Well, I'm going to give you a piece of advice, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的。好了，我要给你一句建议，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.86,0:46:17.22,English,,0,0,0,,And you can test it out for yourself. But if you're feeling sad and\N{\rChinese}你可以自己试试。只要你感到难过，且觉得自己需要去找精神科医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.22,0:46:19.90,English,,0,0,0,,you are feeling depressed and you feel you have to talk to a psychiatrist\N{\rChinese}你感到沮丧，觉得自己需要去找精神科医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.90,0:46:23.30,English,,0,0,0,,and you do so, I will make you bet\N{\rChinese}并且你这么做，我会让你押注
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.30,0:46:26.00,English,,0,0,0,,that the psychiatrist will make it a lot worse.\N{\rChinese}精神科医生会让情况更糟
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.48,0:46:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,You will feel worse after talking to a psychiatrist.\N{\rChinese}你会在去看精神科医生后感觉更糟。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.30,0:46:32.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.70,0:46:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,the reason why is the system is\N{\rChinese}原因是系统的设定
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.62,0:46:39.42,English,,0,0,0,,not designed to cure you of any problems.\N{\rChinese}并非要治愈你的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.60,0:46:43.06,English,,0,0,0,,The system is to make you dependent on authority.\N{\rChinese}系统的作用是让你依赖于权威。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.10,0:46:48.36,English,,0,0,0,,You know that if you feel sad, well, you know what?\N{\rChinese}你知道如果你感到悲伤，那就……你知道是什么吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.64,0:46:50.44,English,,0,0,0,,Just go for a walk, talk to a friend.\N{\rChinese}去散步，跟朋友聊聊。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.56,0:46:53.60,English,,0,0,0,,You'll feel better over time. But the system teaches you, no, if you feel sad,\N{\rChinese}时间一长，你会感觉好些。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.70,0:46:55.44,English,,0,0,0,,go talk to a psychiatrist who will give you drugs.\N{\rChinese}去找精神科医生给你开药。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.20,0:46:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,It's designed to make you dependent on authority.\N{\rChinese}它的设计是让你依赖于权威。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.72,0:47:03.44,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah? I want to ask,\N{\rChinese}是吗？我想问……
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.56,0:47:07.04,English,,0,0,0,,like, in scenario one, in world number one,\N{\rChinese}像，在情景一，世界一中，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.20,0:47:09.94,English,,0,0,0,,wouldn't God also be an authority?\N{\rChinese}不就是上帝也会是权威吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.80,0:47:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,Like, God would also be an authority?\N{\rChinese}像，上帝也会是权威吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.94,0:47:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,That's actually a great question, okay? God is authority.\N{\rChinese}这真是个好问题，好的？上帝是权威。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.34,0:47:20.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. That's actually a great question.\N{\rChinese}好的。这真是个好问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.14,0:47:24.76,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much. So, I have to spend time to explain to you both systems.\N{\rChinese}谢谢你。于是，我得花时间向你解释这两套系统。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.76,0:47:26.02,English,,0,0,0,,And I will do so. But\N{\rChinese}我也会这么做。但
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.02,0:47:28.12,English,,0,0,0,,what's really important about number\N{\rChinese}关于第一种的真正重要的是
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.12,0:47:31.04,English,,0,0,0,,one is the\N{\rChinese}one is the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.04,0:47:34.48,English,,0,0,0,,gods are really\N{\rChinese}神真的很……
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.48,0:47:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,bad people.\N{\rChinese}是好人。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.30,0:47:41.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The gods in number one, the polytheistic system, they fight all the time.\N{\rChinese}好的？第一种的神，泛神论体系的神，他们一直在打仗。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.62,0:47:42.92,English,,0,0,0,,They're vengeful.\N{\rChinese}他们是报复的。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.24,0:47:45.56,English,,0,0,0,,They're angry. They're proud.\N{\rChinese}他们愤怒，骄傲。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.78,0:47:48.92,English,,0,0,0,,But because they're gods, they can get away with it.\N{\rChinese}但因为是神，他们可以逃脱。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.32,0:47:51.92,English,,0,0,0,,And that's the difference between humans and gods.\N{\rChinese}这就是人类与神的区别。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.20,0:47:54.68,English,,0,0,0,,We're all the same. We're all angry.\N{\rChinese}我们都一样，都是愤怒的。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.68,0:47:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,We're all jealous.\N{\rChinese}我们都嫉妒的。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.66,0:48:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,We all fight, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们都在战斗，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.94,0:48:02.86,English,,0,0,0,,But the gods can get away with it.\N{\rChinese}但神能逃脱。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.00,0:48:06.10,English,,0,0,0,,The humans cannot. Gods can do hubris.\N{\rChinese}人类不能。神能自负。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.20,0:48:09.66,English,,0,0,0,,We cannot do hubris. You understand?\N{\rChinese}我们不能自负。你明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.28,0:48:12.18,English,,0,0,0,,So, the idea that, oh,\N{\rChinese}于是，那个想法，哦，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.30,0:48:14.96,English,,0,0,0,,the people in power are benevolent,\N{\rChinese}掌权的人是仁慈的。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.96,0:48:17.98,English,,0,0,0,,the people in power are authority figures who\N{\rChinese}掌权的人是权威人物，他们……
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.98,0:48:22.72,English,,0,0,0,,are after our best interests, that is a new modern concept.\N{\rChinese}他们在乎我们的最佳利益，这才是新的现代概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.24,0:48:26.86,English,,0,0,0,,Before, it was a society of this, this, this, this, this, this, this, this, this, this, this, assume that the king is a king.\N{\rChinese}以前是……这、这、这、这、这、这、这、这、这、这、这，假设国王是国王。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.22,0:48:29.22,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because he's favored by the gods.\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为他得到了众神的青睐。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.86,0:48:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,It's not because he's a good person.\N{\rChinese}不是因为他是好人。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.34,0:48:34.54,English,,0,0,0,,It's not because he's a just ruler. It's just because the gods like him for whatever reason.\N{\rChinese}不是因为他是个正直的君主，只是因为众神喜欢他，随缘而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.66,0:48:38.16,English,,0,0,0,,But guess what? The gods give and the gods take.\N{\rChinese}但你猜怎么回事？神明赐予，神又收回。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.16,0:48:43.80,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe today the king will rule us,\N{\rChinese}也许今天国王会统领我们，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.98,0:48:46.44,English,,0,0,0,,but maybe five years from now he gets unlucky and the gods kill him.\N{\rChinese}也许五年后他不幸，神祸之。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.54,0:48:50.18,English,,0,0,0,,Too bad. If you read Greek mythology, and we will do so in this class, okay?\N{\rChinese}太好了。如果你读过希腊神话，我们在这节课里也会读，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.26,0:48:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,We'll go over into Greek civilization. We'll look at Oedipus.\N{\rChinese}我们会进入希腊文明。我们会看俄狄浦斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.22,0:48:55.76,English,,0,0,0,,We'll look at Homer, the Iliad, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们来看看荷马的《伊利亚特》，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.94,0:48:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,They talk about this all the time.\N{\rChinese}他们一直在谈这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.94,0:48:59.32,English,,0,0,0,,Fate is something that you cannot control.\N{\rChinese}命运是你无法掌控的事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.38,0:49:00.60,English,,0,0,0,,It's something that happens to you.\N{\rChinese}它是发生在你身上的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.70,0:49:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you must live life to your best.\N{\rChinese}于是，你要把生活过得尽善尽美。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.36,0:49:09.36,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So the difference is this.\N{\rChinese}好了？所以区别就在这里。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.70,0:49:14.34,English,,0,0,0,,The difference is in number one,\N{\rChinese}差别在第一点，
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.42,0:49:16.84,English,,0,0,0,,they have a concept called eudaimonia.\N{\rChinese}他们有一个叫做eudaimonia的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.80,0:49:23.60,English,,0,0,0,,If you have no control over your fate,\N{\rChinese}如果你对命运没有掌控，
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.76,0:49:27.74,English,,0,0,0,,if things can happen to you tomorrow\N{\rChinese}如果明天会有事发生在你身上
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.74,0:49:29.66,English,,0,0,0,,that kill you, then\N{\rChinese}那杀死你的，然后
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.66,0:49:33.28,English,,0,0,0,,live your life to the best of your ability today.\N{\rChinese}今天把你的生活过得尽善尽美。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.52,0:49:37.74,English,,0,0,0,,Seize the day. Be the best that you can be today.\N{\rChinese}把握住今天。成为今天最好的自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.12,0:49:41.08,English,,0,0,0,,And that's how you win favor from the gods.\N{\rChinese}这就是你赢得众神青睐的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.24,0:49:44.52,English,,0,0,0,,Eudaimonia, what we call flourishing.\N{\rChinese}eudaimonia，即我们所说的繁荣。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.42,0:49:49.06,English,,0,0,0,,The point of life is to live life to the best of your ability.\N{\rChinese}人生的要点是把生活过得尽善尽美。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.06,0:49:50.34,English,,0,0,0,,And that's how you win favor from the gods. Live it to the best of your ability.\N{\rChinese}这就是你赢得众神青睐的方式。把它过得尽善尽美。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.96,0:49:53.36,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why, guess what, guys?\N{\rChinese}这就是原因，猜猜看，伙计们？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.56,0:49:57.60,English,,0,0,0,,The ancients, the Greeks, they were superior to us.\N{\rChinese}古人，希腊人，他们比我们更优秀。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.82,0:50:00.90,English,,0,0,0,,If you read Greek literature, if you read Greek philosophy,\N{\rChinese}如果你读过希腊文学，如果你读过希腊哲学，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.06,0:50:05.12,English,,0,0,0,,Plato, Homer, Aeschylus, Euboides, they were the best.\N{\rChinese}柏拉图、荷马、埃斯库罗斯、欧布多伊德，他们是最棒的。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.46,0:50:06.78,English,,0,0,0,,Today, we suck.\N{\rChinese}如今我们才是吃瓜的。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.02,0:50:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because instead of eudaimonia, we have pleasure.\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为我们把eudaimonia换成了快乐。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.90,0:50:17.66,English,,0,0,0,,Rather than flourish as creative people,\N{\rChinese}不再像创作型人那样繁荣，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.88,0:50:19.86,English,,0,0,0,,we're like, how do I get to the top? How do I get to the top? How do I get to the top? How do I get to the top? How do I enjoy my life today?\N{\rChinese}我们就像在问：我怎么才能登顶？我怎么才能登顶？我怎么才能登顶？我怎么才能登顶？我今天怎么才能享受生活？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.00,0:50:22.30,English,,0,0,0,,How do I not feel sad?\N{\rChinese}我怎么不感到悲伤？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.08,0:50:27.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So in the first system, even\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以在第一个系统里，虽然听起来我们没有控制，没能动手，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.48,0:50:30.30,English,,0,0,0,,though it sounds like we have no control, we have no agency,\N{\rChinese}though it sounds like we haveno control, we have no agency,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.58,0:50:33.90,English,,0,0,0,,but it inspires us to live to the best of our ability.\N{\rChinese}但它激励我们发挥最佳能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.26,0:50:38.04,English,,0,0,0,,In the second system, we're like, oh, you have complete control over your life.\N{\rChinese}在第二个系统里，我们就像说：哦，你完全掌控自己的生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.16,0:50:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,It enslaves us. Okay?\N{\rChinese}它使我们成为奴隶。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.18,0:50:45.92,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Now,\N{\rChinese}好的。现在，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.96,0:50:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,let's move on to the third and final example.\N{\rChinese}让我们继续到第三个也是最后一个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.86,0:50:52.96,English,,0,0,0,,And I know this is shocking.\N{\rChinese}我知道这很震撼。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.04,0:50:55.32,English,,0,0,0,,I know this is surprising. But\N{\rChinese}我知道这很惊人。但
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.32,0:50:56.90,English,,0,0,0,,over the course of the semester,\N{\rChinese}在整个学期里，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.14,0:51:01.38,English,,0,0,0,,I will give you enough evidence to convince you that this is all true.\N{\rChinese}我会给你足够的证据，让你相信这全是真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.52,0:51:04.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? I'm just setting up the structure and the framework today.\N{\rChinese}好的？我今天只是把结构和框架搭好。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.56,0:51:07.10,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's do now the school.\N{\rChinese}好了。现在来做学校的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.06,0:51:10.96,English,,0,0,0,,Guys, why do we have school?\N{\rChinese}伙计们，学校为什么要开呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.68,0:51:13.58,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we in school? Why?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么在学校？为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.68,0:51:16.46,English,,0,0,0,,Why are you here? What?\N{\rChinese}你们为什么在这里？什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.46,0:51:17.70,English,,0,0,0,,Some place.\N{\rChinese}某个地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.88,0:51:19.64,English,,0,0,0,,Learn and teach. Exactly.\N{\rChinese}学习与教学。正是如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.68,0:51:25.16,English,,0,0,0,,Right. Learn. What else?\N{\rChinese}好的。学习。还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.26,0:51:28.38,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. To get the degree.\N{\rChinese}是的。拿到学位。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.52,0:51:29.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? To get the degree.\N{\rChinese}好的？拿到学位。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.76,0:51:33.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. To graduate.\N{\rChinese}好的。毕业。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.48,0:51:37.56,English,,0,0,0,,What else? Knowledge.\N{\rChinese}还有什么？知识。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.58,0:51:44.76,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yeah.\N{\rChinese}是的。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.56,0:51:51.42,English,,0,0,0,,Excuse me? Excuse me?\N{\rChinese}请问？请问？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.46,0:51:55.62,English,,0,0,0,,I feel like give the power a chance to brainwash someone.\N{\rChinese}我想给力量一次洗脑的机会。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.94,0:51:57.38,English,,0,0,0,,Brainwashing. Okay.\N{\rChinese}洗脑。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.44,0:52:01.72,English,,0,0,0,,Guess what, guys? The correct answer is brainwashing.\N{\rChinese}猜猜看，大家？正确答案是洗脑。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.12,0:52:03.64,English,,0,0,0,,Everything else is a lie.\N{\rChinese}其余全是谎言。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.64,0:52:06.72,English,,0,0,0,,All right. What do you do in the school?\N{\rChinese}好的。你在学校做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.08,0:52:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,You come to class.\N{\rChinese}你来上课。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.92,0:52:11.82,English,,0,0,0,,You listen to a lecture. You read books.\N{\rChinese}你听讲座，读书。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.82,0:52:15.82,English,,0,0,0,,right and then you and then you have to do a test and you have to write a paper\N{\rChinese}好的，然后你又要做测试，写论文
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.28,0:52:17.88,English,,0,0,0,,and then and then\N{\rChinese}然后又
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.88,0:52:23.78,English,,0,0,0,,the teacher gives you a grade that's how you learn right let me ask you this question\N{\rChinese}老师给你打分，这就是学习的方式，来问你个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.78,0:52:27.92,English,,0,0,0,,then throughout most of human history how did we learn\N{\rChinese}然后在大部分人类历史里，我们是怎么学的？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.66,0:52:30.64,English,,0,0,0,,if you become a doctor what did you do\N{\rChinese}如果你成为医生，你会做什么？
